You are building the **MVP of a B2B corporate gifting web application for the Indian market**. HR teams at companies (50–5,000 employees) use it to send gifts at scale — Diwali hampers, onboarding kits, anniversaries — **without collecting recipient addresses**: each recipient gets a secure personal link and enters their own address. The reference user journey (build exactly this): an HR manager signs up, invites a finance colleague, builds a "recipients choose within ₹1,500" campaign for 399 employees from a CSV of just names and emails, funds a prepaid wallet, activates, recipients redeem on their phones with no login, physical orders route to vendors and vouchers issue instantly, exceptions surface to an ops console, unspent money returns to the wallet, and a GST-compliant invoice is generated at the end.

